m just a single example. To improve this, training data can be augmented with synthetic data with unique rules assigned to each sample, which increases task diversity and encourages the model to rely on the provided rules.\n\n**Format Importance:**\nEven input/output pairs with random labels can improve performance, highlighting that the format and distribution of the prompt are as important as the labels themselves.\n\nThe search results suggest that while smaller models do struggle more with in-context learning compared to larger models, careful prompt engineering with worked examples and explicit reasoning steps can improve performance on arithmetic and rule-following tasks."],"durationSeconds":8.556947208000347,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3d80efbe-7ebd-4497-8988-70dd8d0914a2","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
