{"parentUuid":"8b37bb5c-010d-4550-82fc-f12ed09bc1bd","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a8795bfae9e2c2e2b","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_0185VNXaE9mkrNcmuoHo15Np","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XLqVs59pCqZp6gvnF26kAk","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3-8B","prompt":"Extract the official \"Best Practices\" recommended sampling parameters for thinking mode and non-thinking mode (temperature, top_p, top_k, min_p, presence_penalty), the recommended max output / output length (e.g. 32768 or 38912 tokens), warning against greedy decoding in thinking mode, and any guidance on switching between /think and /no_think."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2760,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1068,"cache_read_input_tokens":19005,"output_tokens":395,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1068},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2760,"output_tokens":395,"cache_read_input_tokens":19005,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1068,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1068,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcFsmihomPvmK97gvWAou","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"2062b274-09de-4986-bed9-9437958fc1f5","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:46:16.295Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"2062b274-09de-4986-bed9-9437958fc1f5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"86e3c656-fdf4-40b7-9b8a-223e791a3151","agentId":"a8795bfae9e2c2e2b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XLqVs59pCqZp6gvnF26kAk","type":"tool_result","content":"# Qwen3-8B Best Practices: Sampling & Output Parameters\n\n## Thinking Mode (`enable_thinking=True`)\n**Sampling Parameters:**\n- Temperature: 0.6\n- Top-P: 0.95\n- Top-K: 20\n- Min-P: 0\n\nThe documentation explicitly warns: *\"DO NOT use greedy decoding, as it can lead to performance degradation and endless repetitions.\"*\n\n**Recommended Output Length:** 32,768 tokens for most queries; 38,912 tokens for highly complex problems (math/programming competitions)\n\n## Non-Thinking Mode (`enable_thinking=False`)\n**Sampling Parameters:**\n- Temperature: 0.7\n- Top-P: 0.8\n- Top-K: 20\n- Min-P: 0\n\n**Recommended Output Length:** Same as thinking mode (32,768 tokens standard)\n\n## Presence Penalty\nFor supported frameworks, adjust between 0 and 2 to reduce repetition, though higher values may cause language mixing and slight performance loss.\n\n## Soft Switching: /think and /no_think\nUsers can dynamically control thinking behavior by adding `/think` or `/no_think` tags to prompts during multi-turn conversations. The model follows the most recent instruction. However, when `enable_thinking=False` (hard switch), these soft commands have no effect."}]},"uuid":"68335e66-49aa-4eee-ac9f-d560ea63c7e4","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:46:22.527Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":306769,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Qwen3-8B Best Practices: Sampling & Output Parameters\n\n## Thinking Mode (`enable_thinking=True`)\n**Sampling Parameters:**\n- Temperature: 0.6\n- Top-P: 0.95\n- Top-K: 20\n- Min-P: 0\n\nThe documentation explicitly warns: *\"DO NOT use greedy decoding, as it can lead to performance degradation and endless repetitions.\"*\n\n**Recommended Output Length:** 32,768 tokens for most queries; 38,912 tokens for highly complex problems (math/programming competitions)\n\n## Non-Thinking Mode (`enable_thinking=False`)\n**Sampling Parameters:**\n- Temperature: 0.7\n- Top-P: 0.8\n- Top-K: 20\n- Min-P: 0\n\n**Recommended Output Length:** Same as thinking mode (32,768 tokens standard)\n\n## Presence Penalty\nFor supported frameworks, adjust between 0 and 2 to reduce repetition, though higher values may cause language mixing and slight performance loss.\n\n## Soft Switching: /think and /no_think\nUsers can dynamically control thinking behavior by adding `/think` or `/no_think` tags to prompts during multi-turn conversations. The model follows the most recent instruction. However, when `enable_thinking=False` (hard switch), these soft commands have no effect.","durationMs":6004,"url":"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3-8B"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2062b274-09de-4986-bed9-9437958fc1f5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"8b37bb5c-010d-4550-82fc-f12ed09bc1bd","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"86e3c656-fdf4-40b7-9b8a-223e791a3151","agentId":"a8795bfae9e2c2e2b","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KD6BxA35n84eqcL8ftjBkk","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Qwen3 best practices recommended temperature top_p top_p thinking 0.6 non-thinking 0.7 max output 32768 greedy avoid\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Best Settings to Run Qwen3-30B-A3B Locally\",\"url\":\"https://www.jan.ai/post/qwen3-settings\"},{\"title\":\"Vendor-recommended LLM parameter quick reference - Muxup\",\"url\":\"https://muxup.com/2025q2/recommended-llm-parameter-quick-reference\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3-Next: Run Locally Guide | Unsloth Documentation\",\"url\":\"https://unsloth.ai/docs/models/tutorials/qwen3-next\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B · Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen/Qwen3-0.6B · Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3-0.6B\"},{\"title\":\"Quickstart - Qwen - Read the Docs\",\"url\":\"https://qwen.readthedocs.io/en/latest/getting_started/quickstart.html\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B · Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B\"},{\"title\":\"Temperature control in generation · Issue #524 · QwenLM/Qwen3-VL\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen3-VL/issues/524\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here are the Qwen3 best practices for recommended parameters:\n\n## Thinking Mode Parameters\nFor thinking mode: temperature=0.6, top_p=0.95, top_k=20, min_p=0\n\n## Non-Thinking Mode Parameters\nFor non-thinking mode: temperature=0.7, top_p=0.8, top_k=20, min_p=0\n\n## Output Length\nUse an output length of 32,768 tokens for most queries for the thinking variant, and 16,384 for the instruct variant\n\n## Important: Avoid Greedy Decoding\nGreedy decoding kills thinking mode's output. It'll repeat or get stuck. Stick to sampling, and give it enough token space to finish its thoughts. DO NOT use greedy decoding, as it can lead to performance degradation and endless repetitions.\n\n## Additional Notes\nPresence penalty between 0 and 2 is suggested to reduce endless repetitions. The key distinction is that Qwen3-30B-A3B has two modes: thinking and non-thinking, each mode needs different generation settings.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"0ed28a9c-4e8b-44b5-b1d1-719a11af7513","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:46:22.607Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Qwen3 best practices recommended temperature top_p top_p thinking 0.6 non-thinking 0.7 max output 32768 greedy avoid","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_013L3NGkYbfsknH7Yfejofyx","content":[{"title":"Best Settings to Run Qwen3-30B-A3B Locally","url":"https://www.jan.ai/post/qwen3-settings"},{"title":"Vendor-recommended LLM parameter quick reference - Muxup","url":"https://muxup.com/2025q2/recommended-llm-parameter-quick-reference"},{"title":"Qwen3-Next: Run Locally Guide | Unsloth Documentation","url":"https://unsloth.ai/docs/models/tutorials/qwen3-next"},{"title":"Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B · Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.5-4B"},{"title":"Qwen/Qwen3-0.6B · Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3-0.6B"},{"title":"Quickstart - Qwen - Read the Docs","url":"https://qwen.readthedocs.io/en/latest/getting_started/quickstart.html"},{"title":"Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B · Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B"},{"title":"Temperature control in generation · Issue #524 · QwenLM/Qwen3-VL","url":"https://github.com/QwenLM/Qwen3-VL/issues/524"}]},"Based on the search results, here are the Qwen3 best practices for recommended parameters:\n\n## Thinking Mode Parameters\nFor thinking mode: temperature=0.6, top_p=0.95, top_k=20, min_p=0\n\n## Non-Thinking Mode Parameters\nFor non-thinking mode: temperature=0.7, top_p=0.8, top_k=20, min_p=0\n\n## Output Length\nUse an output length of 32,768 tokens for most queries for the thinking variant, and 16,384 for the instruct variant\n\n## Important: Avoid Greedy Decoding\nGreedy decoding kills thinking mode's output. It'll repeat or get stuck. Stick to sampling, and give it enough token space to finish its thoughts. DO NOT use greedy decoding, as it can lead to performance degradation and endless repetitions.\n\n## Additional Notes\nPresence penalty between 0 and 2 is suggested to reduce endless repetitions. The key distinction is that Qwen3-30B-A3B has two modes: thinking and non-thinking, each mode needs different generation settings."],"durationSeconds":7.810028500000015,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8b37bb5c-010d-4550-82fc-f12ed09bc1bd","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
